# Avoid implicit conversions

- Avoid implicit conversions in hot paths.
- Prefer concrete types/overloads.
- Keep required conversions explicit and local.

```pascal
// ❌ BAD: implicit conversion
procedure SetValue(const V: Variant);
begin
  // ...
end;

SetValue(42);

// ✅ GOOD: overload or explicit conversion
procedure SetValueInt(const V: Integer);
begin
  // ...
end;

SetValueInt(42);

// if Variant is required
SetValue(Variant(42));

// ❌ BAD: implicit string conversion
procedure LogMsg(const S: AnsiString);
begin
  // ...
end;

LogMsg('text'); // default literal may be shortstring

// ✅ GOOD: explicit conversion
LogMsg(AnsiString('text'));
```
